{
  "schema_version": "unistd_abi_promotion_tranche.v1",
  "bead": "bd-5tgwug",
  "trace_id": "bd-5tgwug-unistd-abi-promotion-tranche-v1",
  "description": "Bounded promotion proof for the unistd_abi GNU stack protector row, LFS alias rows, wide/multibyte and wide-stream aliases, getopt, posix_close, and cross-module posix_spawnattr signal accessors that already have strict and hardened ABI evidence.",
  "rationale": "The promoted rows cover the GNU stack protector abort contract, LP64 LFS alias contracts for ftruncate64, lseek64, mmap64, pread64, pwrite64, sendfile64, and truncate64, wide/multibyte and wide-stream symbols cataloged under unistd_abi but implemented in wchar_abi, the native getopt scanner, posix_close over the native close path, and posix_spawnattr signal-set accessors cataloged under unistd_abi but implemented in process_abi. __stack_chk_fail is cataloged in the support matrix under unistd_abi but implemented in fortify_abi; its fixture proof binds the abort behavior while the host-delegation census hits are abort, libio exit-safety, errno, and signal-mask helper artifacts. The LFS symbols alias FrankenLibC's native syscall, mmap, and I/O paths; their census hits are errno/bootstrap helpers plus alias reachability to the native non-64 entrypoints, not host-glibc semantic call-through. The wide/multibyte, wide-stream, and posix_spawnattr symbols have no host-census hits; their ratchet proof binds the cross-module support-matrix catalog rows to direct wchar_abi and process_abi tests. getopt and posix_close census hits are bounded to scanner/native-close helper reachability plus errno/bootstrap helpers.",
  "source_artifacts": [
    "support_matrix.json",
    "tests/conformance/fixtures/unistd_process_filesystem_wave02.json",
    "tests/conformance/fixtures/unistd_process_filesystem_wave13.json",
